value.0: Before you stands a mage who eyes you with suspicion, as if expecting anyone to be an assassin or some such other.
These robes are infused with a darkly, vile magic, and they're splatted with much blood. You absently wonder about their creation.

Many moons ago, the City of Tarkuul existed in a much sinister glory, whence some crusading paladins raized it and naught but the gate bars remained.

You now hold one of these bars, unrusted by time, since Tarkuul's sinister magic has steeped into it's shaft.
This woman seems to be poring through numerous books relating to the elemental planes.

Value.value: You've the look of a strapping adventurer, wot wot!
I am doing research into the strange effects the local insect population has been exhibiting.
They seem to be suffused with elemental fire energy, an oddity for a simple giant ant.
Very interesting. So it seems the magma flows beneath their colony, granting them elemental infusion.. I must ponder this!
Have you made note of all eight ant hills? Finding the queen's lair will likely provide even greater answers.
My thanks for your help with this important bit of research!
Could you make your way to the eastern coast of the isle and make note of all eight ant hills?
If you can get to the deepest part of their colony, that will likely provide the greatest insight!

value.0: A strange looking creature peers at you - Not quite human, but what exactly it is, remains a mystery to most.
A black robe.  Fine for walking about town, and being seen at the Nomad.  Not very practical for battle however.
Pallid skin and a left arm devoid of flesh mark this individual clearly as a Palemaster.
A rather odd-looking man with a half-mop of hair on  his head!
A scythe similar to the one used by the fabled Grim Reaper - a supposed myth...
This red-robed merchant seems to deal in books and magical pages.
This colorful robe is marked all over with patterns that look vaguely like eyes.

Value.value: This strange tree is somehow both dead and not. It emits a necromantic energy.
This tree appears to be a sapling from old Tarkuul. Given unlife, it still continues to grow as though fueled by necromantic power.

value.0: Life and death are the twin faces of eternal existence. To surrender to either one is to resign oneself to obscurity. True power lies in the twilight zone between life and death. By seeking to explore and extend the mortal condition and form, even mortal life itself, knowledge of the world and its infinite complexity are extended. Let no one interfere with the pursuit of such research, for the end result will more than justify the necessary sacrifices along the path. Knowledge is power, and knowledge of life and death brings power over all beings, living and unliving.
